upper\nquadrant\nKey imaging\n▪ Ultrasound is considered the initial imaging test of choice. (first-line diagnosis)\n▪ Computed Tomography (CT) plays a secondary but vital role in the diagnosis of\nacute cholecystitis, especially when the clinical presentation is atypical or\ncomplications are suspected, or when the initial ultrasound is inconclusive\nUltrasound showing acute calculous cholecystitis;\n1. Distended gallbladder full of hypoechoic bile,\n2.Hyperechoic calculus with posterior acoustic\nshadowing (dashed arrow)\n3. Sludge\n4. Thickened gallbladder wall\nCECT showing acute calculous cholecystitis;\n1. Distended gallbladder\n2. Hyperdense calculus\n3. Thickened gallbladder wall\n4. CT rim sign (hepatic hyperemia)\n96"}